ef, 10, pp. 19-27; Linsley, B.K., Messier, R.G., Dunbar, R.B., Assessing between colony oxygen isotope variability in the coral Porites lobata at Clipperton Atoll (1999) Coral Reefs, 18, pp. 13-27; Lough, J.M., A strategy to improve the contribution of coral data to high-resolution paleoclimatology (2004) Palaeogeogr. Palaeoclimatol. Palaeoecol., 204, pp. 115-143; Maier, C., Patzold, J., Bak, R.P.M., The skeletal isotopic composition as an indicator of ecological and physiological plasticity in the coral genus Madracis (2003) Coral Reefs, 22, pp. 370-380; Mann, M.E., Bradley, R.S., Hughes, M.K., Global-scale temperature patterns and climate forcing over the past six centuries (1998) Nature, 392, pp. 779-787; Northern Hemisphere temperatures during the past millennium: Inferences, uncertainties, and limitations (1999) Geophys. Res. Lett., 26, pp. 759-762; McClanahan, T.R., Bleaching damage and recovery potential of Maldivian coral reefs (2000) Mar. Pollut. Bull., 40, pp. 587-597; McConnaughey, T.A., C13 and O18 isotopic disequilibrium in biological carbonates: I. Patterns (1989) Geochim. Cosmochim. Acta, 53, pp. 151-162; McPhaden, M.J., Genesis and evolution of the 1997-98 El Niño (1999) Science, 283, pp. 950-954; Paillard, D., Labeyrie, L., Yiou, P., Macintosh Program performs time-series analysis (1996) Eos Trans. Am. Geophys. Union, 77, p. 379; Reynaud-Vaganay, S., Juillet-Lecherc, A., Jaubert, J., Gattuso, J.-P., Effect of light on skeletal δ13C and δ18O, and interaction with photosynthesis, respiration and calcification in two zooxanthellate scleractinian corals (2001) Paleoclim. Paleoecol., 175, pp. 393-404; Roberts, C.M., Marine biodiversity hotspots and conservation priorities for tropical reefs (2002) Science, 295, pp. 1280-1284; Salingo, J., The 1997/1998 El Niño (1998) Weather, 53, pp. 274-281; Spencer, T., Teleki, K.A., Bradshaw, C., Spalding, M.D., Coral bleaching in southern Seychelles during the 1997-1998 Indian ocean warm event (2000) Mar. Pollut. Bul